// overviewDemos.json — Per-tool "Dummy run" demo specs for the Tools Overview window
// (ToolsOverviewDemos.cs). Every tool's simulated step flow, sample data, and run-log
// lines shown when a user clicks "Dummy run ▶" on a tool card. This is separate from
// overviewDemo.json, which covers the generic simulation engine's own chrome (OverviewDemoTool.cs).
// NOTE: Kind tokens ("multi"/"toggles"/"file"/etc.) and RunLog status tokens
// ("info"/"pass"/"fail"/"skip") stay in code — they're matched in a switch, not shown to users.
// Arrays are stored as numbered objects ("1", "2", ...) since the loader only flattens
// JSON objects, not arrays; ToolsOverviewDemos.cs reconstructs each List<string> in order.
// Run-log lines may carry {count:step}/{sel:step}/{first:step}/{value:step}/{file:step}
// tokens — OverviewDemoTool expands them from the user's live demo selections at run time.
